quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,Does he not know when the tombs are exposed
  100,10,and what is in the breasts is brought to light
  100,11,"Verily, thy Lord upon that day indeed is well aware"
  101,1,The smiting
  101,2,What is the smiting
  101,3,And what shall make thee know what the smiting is
  101,4,The day when men shall be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains shall be like flocks of carded wool
  101,6,And as for him whose balance is heavy
  101,7,he shall be in a well-pleasing life
  101,8,But as for him whose balance is light
  101,9,his dwelling shall be the pit of hell
  101,10,And who shall make thee know what it is
  101,11,a burning fire
  102,1,The contention about numbers deludes you
  102,2,till ye visit the tombs
  102,3,Not so! In the end ye shall know
  102,4,And again not so! In the end ye shall know
  102,5,Not so! Did ye but know with certain knowledge
  102,6,Ye shall surely see hell
  102,7,And again ye shall surely see it with an eye of certainty
  102,8,Then ye shall surely be asked about pleasure
  103,1,By the afternoon
  103,2,"verily, man is in loss"
  103,3,"save those who believe and do right, and bid each other be true, and bid each other be patient"
  104,1,Woe to every slanderous backbiter
  104,2,who collects wealth and counts it
  104,3,He thinks that his wealth can immortalize him
  104,4,Not so! he shall be hurled into ElHutamah
  104,5,And what shall make thee understand what ElHutamah is
  104,6,the fire of God kindled
  104,7,which rises above the hearts
  104,8,"Verily, it is an archway over them"
  104,9,on long-drawn columns
  105,1,Hast thou not seen what thy Lord did with the fellows of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their stratagem lead them astray
  105,3,and send down on them birds in flocks
  105,4,to throw down on them stones of baked clay
  105,5,and make them like blades of herbage eaten down
  106,1,For the uniting of the Qurais
  106,2,uniting them for the caravan of winter and summer
  106,3,So let them serve the Lord of this house
  106,4,who feeds them against hunger and makes them safe against fear
  107,1,Hast thou considered him who calls the judgment a lie
  107,2,He it is who pushes the orphan away
  107,3,and urges not (others) to feed the poor
  107,4,But woe to those who pray
  107,5,and who are careless in their prayers
  107,6,Who pretend
  107,7,and withhold necessaries
  108,1,"Verily, we have given thee El Kauthar"
  108,2,So pray to thy Lord and slaughter (victims)
  108,3,"Verily, he who hates thee shall be childless"
  109,1,"Say, O ye misbelievers"
  109,2,I do not serve what ye serve
  109,3,nor will ye serve what I serve
  109,4,nor will I serve what ye serve
  109,5,nor will ye serve what I serve
  109,6,"ye have your religion, and I have my religion"
  110,1,When there comes God's help and victory
  110,2,And thou shalt see men enter into God's religion by troops
  110,3,"Then celebrate the praises of thy Lord, and ask forgiveness of Him, verily, He is relentant"
  111,1,"Abu Lahebs two hands shall perish, and he shall perish"
  111,2,"His wealth shall not avail him, nor what he has earned"
  111,3,He shall broil in a fire that flames
  111,4,and his wife carrying faggots
  111,5,on her neck a cord of palm fibres
  112,1,"Say, He is God alone"
  112,2,God the Eternal
  112,3,He begets not and is not begotten
  112,4,Nor is there like unto Him any one
  113,1,"Say, I seek refuge in the Lord of the daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of what He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the night when it cometh on
  113,4,and from the evil of the blowers upon knots
  113,5,and from the evil of the envious when he envies
  114,1,"Say, I seek refuge in the Lord of men"
  114,2,the King of men
  114,3,the God of men
  114,4,"from the evil of the whisperer, who slinks off"
  114,5,who whispers into the hearts of men
  114,6,from ginns and men